------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4420 | antanas | 2015-12-08 14:07:15 +0200 (Tue, 08 Dec 2015) | 10 lines

cod-tools/ (antanas@echidna.ibt.lt)
Enhancement: modifying 'listdiff' targets to sort the list of failed 
tests by test names (9th column of the 'ls' command output). NOTE: the 
'sort -k9 | uniq' is intentionally writen as two separate commands and 
should not be replaced by the 'sort -u -k9' since the latter not only 
sorts the output of 'ls' by the 9th column but also uniquifies the 
output based on the same criterion. This is dangerous since, it 
would break and output only a single failed tests in case the output 
format of the 'ls' command changes.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4419 | antanas | 2015-12-08 13:32:05 +0200 (Tue, 08 Dec 2015) | 7 lines

cod-tools/ (antanas@echidna.ibt.lt)
Bug fix: replacing recursive make calls in the 'listdiff' target with a 
single 'find' call from the './src' directory. This removed the 
duplicate entries from the list of failed test and allowed to avoid 
explicitly listing all directories that need to be traversed with the 
recursive make calls. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------
